    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>4 large bell peppers, halved and seeds removed</li>
            <li>1 cup cooked quinoa or rice</li>
            <li>1 can (15 oz) black beans, drained and rinsed</li>
            <li>1 cup corn kernels (fresh, frozen, or canned)</li>
            <li>1 cup diced tomatoes</li>
            <li>1 cup shredded vegan cheese</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ground cumin</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon chili powder</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon garlic powder</li>
            <li>Salt and black pepper, to taste</li>
            <li>Fresh cilantro or parsley for garnish</li>
            <li>Optional toppings: avocado slices, salsa, vegan sour cream</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).</li>
            <li>Place the halved bell peppers in a baking dish, cut side up.</li>
            <li>In a large bowl, mix together the cooked quinoa or rice, black beans, corn, diced tomatoes, vegan cheese, cumin, chili powder, garlic powder, salt, and black pepper.</li>
            <li>Spoon the filling into each bell pepper half, pressing down gently to pack the filling.</li>
            <li>Cover the baking dish with foil and bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the peppers are tender.</li>
            <li>Remove the foil and bake for an additional 10 minutes to melt the vegan cheese and lightly brown the tops.</li>
            <li>Remove from the oven and let cool for a few minutes.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh cilantro or parsley, and serve the Stuffed Bell Peppers with optional toppings like avocado slices, salsa, or vegan sour cream.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Stuffed Bell Peppers!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

